We stayed in one of the lofts and initially had some temperature issues but they were addressed quickly.	The roof top pool was like a spa and even though it was 102 degrees, it felt very comfortable because of the fans and the misting system.	We especially found the room service to be timely and tasty (yes, we even had breakfast by the pool one day!).	The room was surprisingly small and the bed was terrible, i liked the idea of a round bed as it is unique but it was very awkward and felt cheap..not a luxury collection standard.